				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Vhaksiz the Shade in PoN, any suggestions?<a name="27056"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 11 04 4:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Took Him down yesterday on server up for a guild cleric.  Couple of things you need. At the upper 50 to mid 60 range, I recommend taking two to three full groups for clearing the caves of hobgoblins.  There are a good amount of then to clear. Once up top taking the right path, have monk / bard pull the horses around the edge holding close to the wall so you dont aggro vhaksiz.  once clear, Make sure you have two healers for the main tank, and a rampage healer for the off tank / rampage tank.  We had a 10,500 hp warrior and just one cleric for him and teh cleric had to do lots of complete heals. Vhaksiz cannot be slowed so expect to rotate some heals on the main tank. His MR is really high as well. I got a lot of vamp talon resists and life taps dont get resisted that much. He had a lot more hp than I expected for his lvl ( 65 ) but is a pretty easy steady fight.  As long as you keep aggro on your main tank and have the mana to keep em healed its just a matter of time.. oh yeah did not enrage.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
